HEADWORD: Perigenesis
<hw>Per`i*gen"e*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>A theory which explains inheritance by the transmission of the type
of growth force possessed by one generation to another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perigenetic</ent>⟦br⟧
